    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Delete Coincident Constraint</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <list id="3" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Body Table" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">SHIFT+CLICK</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;"> a sketch-element with a Coincident</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Body Text">constraint</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">The </text><text styleclass="Body Text">sketch-element</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> and </text><text styleclass="VariableName">CoincidentPtoP, </text><text style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">&#32;</text><text styleclass="VariableName">CoincidentPtoL</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, or </text><text styleclass="VariableName">CoincidentPtoC </text><text styleclass="Body Text">constraint</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> show in the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Selection-Window</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">In the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Selection-Window</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">:</text></para>
          <list id="3" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">Right-click the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">CoincidentLtoL</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">, </text><text styleclass="VariableName">CoincidentPtoP, </text><text style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">&#32;</text><text styleclass="VariableName">CoincidentPtoL</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, or </text><text styleclass="VariableName">CoincidentPtoC </text><text styleclass="Body Text">constraint</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">Click </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Delete </text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">in the contextual-menu</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Notes on Coincident Constraints: </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="1" colcount="1" style="width:auto;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:top;">
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName">Coincident Constraint</text>, <text styleclass="VariableName">Points</text>, and <text styleclass="VariableName">Degrees-of-Freedom</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text style="font-style:normal;">A </text><text styleclass="Element">Point</text><text styleclass="Interface2">* </text><text style="font-style:normal;">has two degrees-of-freedom.</text></para>
          <list id="4" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text style="font-style:normal;">If you add</text><text styleclass="Bullets" style="font-style:normal;"> a </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Coincident Constraint</text><text styleclass="Bullets" style="font-style:normal;"> between a </text><text styleclass="Element">Point</text><text styleclass="Bullets" style="font-style:normal;"> and a </text><text styleclass="Element">Line</text><text styleclass="Bullets" style="font-style:normal;"> &#160;(</text><text styleclass="VariableName">CoincidentPtoL</text><text styleclass="Bullets" style="font-style:normal;">) you remove 1 degrees-of-freedom</text><text styleclass="VariableName">. </text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text style="font-style:normal;">Then, you attempt to add a </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Coincident Constraint</text><text style="font-style:normal;"> between two </text><text styleclass="Element">Points</text><text style="font-style:normal;"> (</text><text styleclass="VariableName">CoincidentPtoP</text><text style="font-style:normal;">) you will attempt to remove 2 degrees-of-freedom.</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Bullets">However, it is not possible to </text><text styleclass="Bullets" style="font-style:normal;">remove three(3) degrees-of-freedom from a </text><text styleclass="Element">Point</text><text styleclass="Bullets" style="font-style:normal;">. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text style="font-style:normal;">Therefore, the </text><text styleclass="Element">Points</text><text style="font-style:normal;"> will </text><text styleclass="VariableName">not</text><text style="font-style:normal;"> move together when you add the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">CoincidentPtoP</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">To correct the problem, you must delete the <text styleclass="VariableName">CoincidentPtoL - see </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Menu-Constraints" anchor="DeleteConstraintGeneral" styleclass="VariableName">How to delete a Constraint</link></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text" style="page-break-before:always;"></para>
